<p>My Child:</p>

<p>USES TOOTHPASTE CONTAINING 1350ppm - 1500ppm OF FLUORIDE?</p>

<p>Uses the correct toothpaste amount:</p>

<p>A smear= child under age of 3</p>

<p>A pea size= child over age of 3</p>

<p>Brushes for two minutes at a time</p>

<p>Brushes their teeth twice a day:</p>

<p>Once in the morning + one other time in the day</p>

<p>Spit out toothpaste instead of rinsing their mouth with water to ensure that some toothpaste remains on their teeth</p>

<p>Visited the dentist before turning 1 years old</p>

<p>Visits the dentist regularly (Every 6 months-1 year)</p>

<p>Eats sweet treats at meal times instead of snacking throughout the day.</p>
